    "created_at": "2018-06-06T21:21:16Z",
    "updated_at": "2018-06-06T21:24:49Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "This is just a documentation problem. The port is indeed populated, just after the call to e.g. BuildAndStart().\r\n\r\nMy suggestion is that the documentation could change from:\r\n\r\n> selected_port[out] If not nullptr, gets populated with the port number bound to the grpc::Server for the corresponding endpoint after it is successfully bound, 0 otherwise.\r\n\r\nto\r\n\r\n> selected_port[out] If not nullptr, gets populated with the port number bound to the grpc::Server for the corresponding endpoint after it is successfully bound **by BuildAndStart()**, 0 otherwise. **AddListeningPort does not modify this pointer.**\r\n\r\nThis works:\r\n\r\n    grpc::ServerBuilder builder;\r\n    int selected_port = -1;\r\n    builder.AddListeningPort(server_endpoint, grpc::InsecureServerCredentials(),\r\n                             &selected_port);\r\n    builder.RegisterService(&api_server);\r\n    // This call populates selected_port\r\n    std::unique_ptr<grpc::Server> server = builder.BuildAndStart();\r\n\r\n    if (selected_port <= 0) {\r\n      std::cerr << \"Failed AddListeningPort: \" << server_endpoint << std::endl;\r\n      return EXIT_FAILURE;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n"
  },
